  "text": "It is of interest to note that of almost 70 clones of ex vivo tumor variants analyzed, apparent heterozygosity is found in only five clones. Since mutation in both alleles in the majority of the clones is unlikely, we believe the J558-Neo tumor cells probably have only one copy of the P1A gene to begin with. Since P1A was recently mapped to the X chromosome [CITATION_1] , the hemizygosity of the gene may be due to the fact that the tumor cells are The apparent heterozygosity may be due to the accidental seeding of two independent clones into one well.",
